oai_dc:dc.dc:title: STEEP WAVE DIFFRACTION BY A SUBMERGED CYLINDER
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Chacaltana, J.T. Aquije
da Silva, A.F. Teles
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: cylinder
diffraction
steep wave
submerged cylinder
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The steep wave diffraction by a fixed circular submerged cylinder is numerically simmulated as a completely nonlinear time domain evolution from an initial condition. Attention is focused on two aspects of the problem. The first is a study of the perturbation introduced by the cylinder on the wave field; the second is a study of the hydrodynamic forces on the cylinder due to the waves.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 24 (1994): Proceedings of 24th Conference on Coastal Engineering, Kobe, Japan, 1994.
